        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — Dorcatherium maliki n. sp. from Küçükçekmece West, Turkey: A, m1-m3 dex, MNHN.F.TRQ748 in lingual (up), occlusal (middle), and buccal (down) views; B, p3-p4 sin, ITU371 in occlusal (reversed-up) and buccal (down) views; C, P2 sin, MNHN.F.TRQ759 in occlusal view; D, P4 sin, ITU no No. in buccal (left), occlusal (middle), and lingual (right) views; E, dp2 dex, MNHN.F.TRQ779 in occlusal (up) and buccal (down) view; F, m2 sin, MNHN.F.TRQ766 in oc- clusal view; G, dP4 dex, MNHN.F.TRQ763 in occlusal view; H, p4 sin, MNHN.F.TRQ768 in occlusal view; I, m3 dex, MNHN.F.TRQ784 in occlusal view; J, M2 sin, MNHN.F.TRQ751 in occlusal view;K, m2 dex,MNHN.F.TRQ783 in occlusal view;L, calcaneum,MNHN.F.TRQ703 in medial view;M, distal radius,MNHN.F.TRQ733 in distal view; N, metatarsal III+IV, MNHN.F.TRQ741 in plantar (left) and dorsal (right) view; O, distal tibia and talus, MNHN.F.TRQ716, TRQ717 in dorsal view; P, tibia, MNHN.F.TRQ718 in dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 cm." ;
